# Housing App — Backend

Express + JavaScript + Prisma (MongoDB) API for the rental marketplace.

## Setup

1. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   npm install
   ```

2. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill in your values:
   ```bash
   ```
   - `DATABASE_URL`: your MongoDB Atlas connection string (or a local Mongo **replica set** — Prisma requires replica set mode, a standalone `mongod` will not work).
   - `JWT_SECRET`: any long random string.

3. Push the Prisma schema to your database (MongoDB uses `db push`, not `migrate`):
   ```bash
   npm run prisma:generate
   npm run prisma:push
   ```

4. Start the dev server:
   ```bash
   npm run dev
   ```

Server runs at `http://localhost:3000`. Health check: `GET /api/health`.

## API overview

| Method | Route | Auth | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | /api/auth/register | – | Create account |
| POST | /api/auth/login | – | Log in, returns JWT |
| GET | /api/auth/me | Bearer | Get current user |
| GET | /api/listings | – | Search/filter listings (query params: city, propertyType, minPrice, maxPrice, bedrooms, page, limit) |
| GET | /api/listings/mine | Bearer (LANDLORD) | Listings owned by current user |
| GET | /api/listings/:id | – | Single listing |
| POST | /api/listings | Bearer (LANDLORD) | Create listing |
| PATCH | /api/listings/:id | Bearer (owner) | Update listing |
| DELETE | /api/listings/:id | Bearer (owner) | Delete listing |
| GET | /api/favorites | Bearer | Current user's saved listings |
| POST | /api/favorites/:listingId | Bearer | Save a listing |
| DELETE | /api/favorites/:listingId | Bearer | Unsave a listing |
| POST | /api/inquiries | Bearer | Send inquiry about a listing |
| GET | /api/inquiries/mine | Bearer | Inquiries sent by current user |
| GET | /api/inquiries/received | Bearer (LANDLORD) | Inquiries on current user's listings |
| PATCH | /api/inquiries/:id | Bearer (owner) | Update inquiry status |

## Auth

Send the JWT from login/register as a Bearer token on protected routes:
```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```
